collections. The distribution file may be uploaded to Bulletin
Board Systems or FTP servers.  If you want to distribute this program
you *must* use the original distribution archive `TextLabel.lha'.

    For products that use the textlabel.image file, only that file
needs to be distributed.


LICENSE

   When using textlabel.image class for `public domain' or
`shareware' software, the following license aplies.

  1) Note in the program and documentation that textlabel.image is
     Copyright © 1994, 1995 hartmut Goebel
  2) You must give me a copy (address below) of the software it is
     used in which includes different versions of the software that
     use the image.  There should be no cost to me.  The purpose is
     to track the image's usage for future developments.

  The textlabel.image class may not be included or used in
commercial programs (exept shareware) unless by written permission
from the author.  Since a commercial license will be pretty cheap, I
recommend to contact me.


   *Neither* of the programs *nor* the documentation (nor parts of
it) may be used on any machine which is used for the research,
development, construction, testing or production of weapons or other
military applications.  This also includes any machine which is used
for training persons for *any* of the above mentioned purposes.


